Title: Threshold amplitudes in field theories and integrable systems

Authors: Alexander Gorsky,Konstantin Selivanov

Comments: 8 pages,Latex, ps is available at

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A11 (1996) 1597-1604

We discuss the threshold tree amplitudes in diverse nonintegrable quantumfield theories in the framework of integrability. The amplitudes are related tosome Baker functions defined on the auxiliary spectral curves and thenullification phenomena are shown to allow a topological interpretation.